SIMPLE: twelfth
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Twelfth
<hw>Twelfth</hw> <pr>(tw⟦ecr⟧lfth)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[For
<ets>twelft</ets>, OE. <ets>twelfte</ets>, AS. <ets>twelfta</ets>. See
<er>Twelve</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Next in order after the
eleventh; coming after eleven others; -- the ordinal of
<xex>twelve</xex>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Constituting, or being one of, twelve equal parts
into which anything is divided.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Twelfth</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Twelfth
<hw>Twelfth</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>The quotient of a unit
divided by twelve; one of twelve equal parts of one whole.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>The next in order after the eleventh.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <fld>(Mus.)</fld> <def>An interval comprising an octave
and a fifth.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Twelfth-cake</ent>⟦br⟧
